Output: E. 1-n/n is incorrect, because if n = 0 there is a 100% chance no one will be invited. If n is anything above 0 n/n is a 10. So 1-n/ n must follow a 1-10 rule, which is always less than 10%, which also contradict the rule that if all people in a certain group are invited there is a 1-0 chance one is not invited. A would also make no sense since 0 is excluded as well. The correct result of 1 - n/n is 0 if at least one person was invited, and 1 if at most one person was invited. This makes E the correct answer.
